START
Good evening. Let’s take a moment to reflect on your day.

Q: Where did most of your energy go today?
→ Dealing with problems

Q: When things didn’t go as expected today, what felt most natural?
→ Feel frustrated at the situation

Reflection:
Days like this can feel out of your hands. Still, somewhere in there, you made a call — even if it was small.

Q: What made it harder to act in that moment?
→ I kept second-guessing myself

Reflection:
There was a gap between knowing what to do and acting on it. That gap is where most days get shaped.

Bridge:
How you handled things is one part of the story. Let’s look at what you gave.

Q: In your interactions today, what did you find yourself focusing on?
→ Wanting recognition for my work

Reflection:
Wanting recognition is natural. But shifting your focus to what you give often changes how those moments feel.

Q: What made that moment stand out to you?
→ It changed how I was feeling

Reflection:
Some moments stand out because of what you gave — whether you noticed it then or not.

Bridge:
Let’s widen the lens a bit.

Q: When you think about today, who was at the center of your attention?
→ Mostly me

Reflection:
When everything sits on you, the day can feel heavier than it is. Sometimes, there’s more happening around you than it seems.

Q: What did you notice about them in that moment?
→ Their actions affected how I felt

Reflection:
Some moments shift when you look beyond your own experience.

SUMMARY:
Today, you leaned external when things got difficult, focused on entitlement in your actions, and saw the day through self. That combination shapes how your day felt.

END
That’s enough for today.
